<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78863a32-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s718p"><num value="718p">§ 718p.</num><heading> Authority to issue electronic duck stamps</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id78863a33-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s718p/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may authorize any State to issue electronic stamps in accordance with this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id78863a34-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s718p/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Consultation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall implement this section in consultation with State management agencies.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id78863a35-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/239/s3">Pub. L. 113–239, § 3</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2848">128 Stat. 2848</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
